Hi [First Name],

Every curriculum decision eventually faces this question:
=E2=80=9CHow does this align with our standards?=E2=80=9D
School boards want to know. Accreditation bodies require it. Parents ask abou=
t it. And rightfully so: standards alignment ensures students are learning wh=
at they need to succeed, whether they=E2=80=99re preparing for university, in=
ternational exams, or future careers.
For computing education, the key standards are ISTE (International Society fo=
r Technology in Education), CSTA K-12 CS (Computer Science Teachers Associati=
on), and UN SDG 4 (Quality Education) =E2=80=94 plus regional requirements li=
ke Cambridge IGCSE, IB, and AP pathways.
Here=E2=80=99s how Level Up Through Digital Discoveries delivers:
Independently Reviewed Every 2 Years =E2=80=94 Level Up isn=E2=80=99t just se=
lf-proclaimed =E2=80=9Cstandards-aligned.=E2=80=9D It=E2=80=99s independently=
 reviewed by education experts every two years to ensure alignment with evolv=
ing standards and best practices.
Built on ISTE Standards =E2=80=94 every lesson maps to the ISTE standards for=
 students: Empowered Learner, Digital Citizen, Knowledge Constructor, Innovat=
ive Designer, Computational Thinker, Creative Communicator, and Global Collab=
orator.
Aligned with the CSTA K-12 CS Framework =E2=80=94 Level Up covers all five co=
re concepts: Computing Systems; Networks and the Internet; Data and Analysis;=
 Algorithms and Programming; and Impacts of Computing. Progression follows CS=
TA=E2=80=99s developmental approach.
Supports UN SDG 4 (Quality Education) =E2=80=94 equitable access to computing=
 education, digital literacy as a fundamental skill, and support for bilingua=
l and multilingual learners.
Prepares Students for Global Pathways =E2=80=94 Cambridge IGCSE Computer Scie=
nce, IB Computer Science (SL/HL), AP Computer Science Principles, and AP Comp=
uter Science A.
Want proof? We=E2=80=99ve created detailed mapping documents that show exactl=
y where each standard is addressed across the K-12 curriculum.
Download: Complete ISTE Standards Mapping (PDF) =E2=86=92
Download: Complete CSTA Standards Mapping (PDF) =E2=86=92
Download: How to Pitch Level Up to Your Leadership (1-Page Brief) =E2=86=92
These documents are designed for exactly the conversation you=E2=80=99ll have=
 with your school board, head of school, or curriculum committee. They answer=
 the alignment question definitively.
P.S. =E2=80=94 The =E2=80=9CHow to Pitch Level Up to Your Leadership=E2=80=9D=
 brief includes talking points, FAQs, and the business case for comprehensive=
 K-12 computing education. Use it to make the case internally.

Download: Complete ISTE Standards Mapping (PDF): https://info.mheducation.com=
/int_ict

